%N A084761 A sequence of primes such that (a(n)-a(n-1)) / (a(n-1)-a(n-2)) is a unique integer.
%C A084761 The sequence of successive difference ratios (a(n)-a(n-1)) / (a(n-1)-a(n-2)) is 2,1,3,4,5,6,8,7,...
%C A084761 Conjecture: every number is a term of this sequence, or for every number r there exists some k such that (a(k)-a(k-1)) / (a(k-1)-a(k-2)) = r.
%C A084761 Question: What is the longest string of consecutive integers in this sequence (of successive differences)?
%e A084761 (a(5)-a(4)) / (a(4)-a(3)) = (13-7) / (7-5) = 3. Then it is to be taken care of that this ratio is not 3 for any other set of three successive terms.
